# SDR Screener ‚Äî Frontend

Stack: **Next.js 15 App Router**, **TypeScript**, **Tailwind**, **shadcn/ui**, **Supabase client** (`@supabase/ssr`).

## Product constraints (v1)

- Recruiters **save job descriptions** (paste JD or requirements list), **select one via dropdown** on upload, and **add/delete** JDs. No rubric editor.
- Pages: `/login`, `/job-descriptions`, `/upload`, `/candidates`, `/candidates/[id]`.
- Show `processing` ‚Üí `complete` via Supabase Realtime on the detail page.

## Structure

| Path | Use |
|------|-----|
| `app/(auth)/` | Login only |
| `app/(dashboard)/` | Job descriptions, upload, candidates (protected) |
| `app/(dashboard)/job-descriptions/` | List + add/edit/delete saved JDs |
| `components/{auth,upload,candidates,job-descriptions,layout}/` | Feature UI |
| `components/ui/` | shadcn primitives only |
| `hooks/` | `use-upload`, `use-screening-realtime`, `use-job-descriptions` |

## Patterns

- Functional components; extract logic to hooks under `hooks/`.
- Use **server components** for data fetch where possible; **client components** only when needed (forms, Realtime, file upload).
- Call `POST /api/upload/presign` then upload **directly to Supabase Storage** ‚Äî never send file bytes through Next.js API routes.
- After upload, call `POST /api/screen` with `job_description_id`, paths, and candidate metadata.
- Import types from `lib/types/`; do not duplicate screening JSON shapes in components.

## Job descriptions UI

- **`/job-descriptions`**: table or cards of saved JDs (`title`, snippet of `body`, `updated_at`). Actions: **Add**, **Edit**, **Delete** (confirm dialog; warn if JD is in use by past candidates).
- **Add/Edit form**: `title` (required, short) + `body` textarea (required) ‚Äî placeholder: *"Paste the full job description or a list of requirements"*.
- **`/upload`**: **dropdown** (`Select` / shadcn) listing user's JDs by `title`. Required when at least one JD exists. Link: *"Manage job descriptions"* ‚Üí `/job-descriptions`. If no JDs exist, show empty state + CTA to create one first.
- **Candidate detail**: show JD `title` used for that screening (fetch via `job_description_id` on candidate).

## UI

- Strengths/weaknesses: show dimension label, score 0‚Äì10 bar, and evidence text.
- Use `lucide-react` for icons; keep layouts minimal and recruiter-focused.

## Avoid

- Adding org/team/billing features unless explicitly requested.
- One-off JD paste on upload without saving ‚Äî always use saved JDs + dropdown (except dev/testing).
- Putting OpenAI/Whisper calls in the frontend.
- Proxying video through API routes.
